### 3. Types of Critical Points for 2d Systems

We can use the eigenvalues and eigenvectors to anticipate what solutions around $\underline{critical points}$ (y' = 0, steady states) look like. This will be really useful for controls!

If the eigenvalues are $\underline{real}$ and distinct:

\begin{align}
\begin{equation}
\lambda_1 > \lambda_2 > 0
\end{equation}

improper node (unstable)

\begin{equation}
\lambda_1 < \lambda_2 < 0
\end{equation}

improper node (stable)

\begin{equation}
\lambda_1 > 0, & \lambda_2 < 0
\end{equation}

saddle
\end{align}
